Licensing Agreement for "Doog and Friends"

This project operates under a dual-licensing model. You may choose the license or licenses that best fits your needs based on the type of content you are using and creating:

I. Software, Video Games, and Interactive Media
For all codebases, executable files, and interactive logic:

The GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPL-3.0): Available at no cost. Under this license, any software, video games, and interactive media including all assets, codebases, executable files, and interactive logic along with user created modifications and addons that contain assets, codebases, executable files, and interactive logic incorporating Doog and Friends creative property, assets, code, programs, binaries, shared libraries, and custom langauges made by the authors of Doog and Friends including programing, scripting, markup, and assembly langauges must be open-sourced and shared under the GPL-3.0. The full license can be found here: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt

Commercial License: If you wish to use Doog and Friends creative property in a closed-source project or do not wish to be bound by the "copyleft" requirements of the GPL, please contact the author at [keleferreria@gmail.com] to negotiate a commercial license. Offered commercial licensing models include; perpetual, subscription/DAFaaS, and pay as you go/for what you use.

II. Books, Music, Animation, and Film
For all narrative works, television shows, motion pictures, music, and static artistic assets incorporating Doog and Friends creative property:

Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 (CC BY-SA 4.0): Available at no cost. Under this license, you must provide attribution to the author, and any derivative creative works must be released under this same license. The Human-Readable Summary can be found here: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

Commercial License: If you wish to use these characters, stories, or assets in a proprietary project (where you do not wish to share-alike) or for large-scale commercial distribution, please contact the author at [keleferreria@gmail.com] for a private license. Offered commercial licensing models include; perpetual, subscription/DAFaaS, and pay as you go/for what you use.
